                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d187">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/806: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-14T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1922—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>95. Your January 13, 4 p.m.<note n="90" xml:id="d187fn90">See preceding
                        footnoe.</note> In an interview with the President this morning he expressed
                    his gratification at the proposed action and stated that the invitation when
                    extended would be accepted with pleasure without qualification.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sterling</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
